      <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:baseline;"><span class="fin-sub">Monthly gap</span><strong style="font-size:24px;color:${monthlyGap ? '#b91c1c' : '#1f4d3f'};">${monthlyGap ? fmt(monthlyGap) : '$0'}</strong></div>
      <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:baseline;"><span class="fin-sub">Six-month gap</span><strong style="font-size:24px;color:${sixMonthGap ? '#b91c1c' : '#1f4d3f'};">${fmt(sixMonthGap)}</strong></div>
      <div class="fin-alert ${monthlyGap ? 'danger' : 'info'}" style="margin:4px 0 0;">
        <strong>Household contribution target:</strong> ${fmt(contributionTarget)}/mo closes the current budget gap before debt payoff. If that cannot happen, the dashboard should force a choice: defer lower-priority bills, reduce costs, or use a temporary family/settlement/tax bridge.
